# Important Definitions

## Variable

A named memory location used to store data.

---

## Data Type

Specifies the type of data that can be stored and how much memory is allocated.

---

## Primitive Data Type

Stores actual values directly.

---

## Non-Primitive Data Type

Stores references to objects.

---

## Identifier

A name given to program elements such as variables, methods, classes, and objects.

---

## Literal

The actual value assigned to a variable.

---

## Space Complexity

Measures the additional memory required by an algorithm as the input size increases.

